      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, season your <strong>hake fillet[s] </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Lay the <strong>seasoned hake</strong> over the <strong>spinach & tomato orzo</strong>, top with the <strong>grated cheese</strong> and cook, covered, for 5 min or until the hake is cooked through – this is your <strong>one-pot</strong> <strong>creamy hake florentine</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked when it turns opaque and flakes easily!</p>",
